><div class = \"text-block\">: for >500,000 cells, use DNA\/RNA Universal AllPrep kit; for <500,000 cells, use Qiagen DNA\/RNA AllPrep Micro kit.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">a. Centrifuge cells, then carefully remove all supernatant by aspiration.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">b. Loosen pellet by flicking and add RLT Plus buffer (prepared with\u00a0\u00a0 Beta-mercaptoethanol)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>< 5\u00a0\u00a0x 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span>cells, <\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span>5 x 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span>\u2013 1 x 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">7<\/span><span>cells, <\/span><\/div><br\/><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">2.<\/span><span> Pipet the lysate directly into a QIAshredder spin column and centrifuge for 2 min at maximum speed.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">3.<\/span><span> Continue with AllPrep protocol, or snap freeze and store at <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  for future use.<\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"8E8A11A0DE8211EBB6E59FB2DBD5964B","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":350,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"94AD1D20DE8211EBB6E59FB2DBD5964B","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":600,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"BC4008C0DE8211EBB6E59FB2DBD5964B","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":-80,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1232836,"guid":"3A999CABF9014213BD0161F99BF3B7A7","previous_id":1232835,"previous_guid":"84D84E1F46E24163BBFFAAABF3D65CF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"56B917AE88D847FDB7C84D31EE3A5913","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Links to kits used in post-processing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"20FDD7F49A7D493D9C3FEBE607567545","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">1.<\/span><span> All recent samples (using 750pg input) were processed using Takara Pico kit with <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.takarabio.com\/documents\/User%20Manual\/SMARTer%20Stranded%20Total%20RNA\/SMARTer%20Stranded%20Total%20RNA-Seq%20Kit%20v2%20-%20Pico%20Input%20Mammalian%20User%20Manual_050619.pdf\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Total RNA-Seq Kit v2<\/span><\/a><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">2.<\/span><span> All samples prior to 2020 (used 100ng input) were processed using <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/support.illumina.com\/content\/dam\/illumina-support\/documents\/documentation\/chemistry_documentation\/samplepreps_truseq\/truseq-stranded-total-rna-workflow\/truseq-stranded-total-rna-workflow-reference-1000000040499-00.pdf\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Illumina TruSeq Stranded Total RNA Library prep Gold<\/span><\/a><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"D95AFCC626644BC2BA4476B09157C46D","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\">The cells go through the All Prep kit to get RNA and then utilized for bulk RNA-seq processing.\u00a0From this preparation, we also acquire DNA which is used for Whole Genome Bisulphide Sequencing (WGBS).<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\"><\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":"","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Bulk RNA sequencing (RNA-seq) is a quantitative method used to interrogate the transcriptome of a biological sample at a given point in time. This protocol describes a method for generating bulk RNA-seq libraries from human islet material. This method also allows for isolation of genomic DNA, which can be used for additional assays such as whole genome bisulphite sequencing.<\/span><\/div><br\/><br\/><br\/><\/div>","changed_on":1629117847}